book:

MessagePack
MsgPack


 &reftitle.intro;

  MsgPack is a drop in replacement for the standard PHP serializer and comparable to
  igbinary with the main difference being
  that MsgPack is supported in different languages.
  Instead of the time and space consuming textual representation used by PHP's serialize,
  MsgPack stores PHP data structures in a compact binary form.
  Memory savings are significant when using memcached, APCu,
  or similar memory based storages for serialized data.
  The typical reduction in storage requirements are around 50%.
  The exact percentage depends on the data.



